---
title: Chicken, Arugula & Blue Cheese Salad with Roasted Carrots, Walnuts & Potato Wedges
description: Cool blue cheese dressing meets warm roasted carrots in this hearty chicken and arugula salad. Sprinkle walnuts over the top for a nutty, crunchy garnish that pairs perfectly with the savory, tangy blue cheese. A side of roasted potato wedges are perfect for dipping in any leftover dressing.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/67291f1c6db9cd4df46dfd62-06263a2c.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/67291f1c6db9cd4df46dfd62-en-US.pdf
cuisine: North America
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/chicken-arugula-and-blue-cheese-salad-67291f1c6db9cd4df46dfd62
time required: 35 minutes
servings: 2
nutrition:
  calories: 590 kcal
  fat: 26 g
  saturated fat: 4.5 g
  carbohydrates: 51 g
  sugar: 12 g
  protein: 38 g
  fiber: 8 g
  sodium: 510 mg
author: HelloFresh
course: main course
---

Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat #oven{} to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Trim, peel, and cut @carrots{12%ounce} on a diagonal into 1/2-inch-thick pieces. Cut @potatoes{12%ounce} into 1/2-inch-thick wedges.

Toss carrots on one side of a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @cooking oil{}, @salt{}, and @pepper{} (spread out across entire sheet for 4). Toss potatoes on empty side of baking sheet with a drizzle of @cooking oil{}, @salt{}, and @pepper{} (use a separate baking sheet for 4). Roast on top rack until tender, ~{20-25%minutes}. (For 4, roast potatoes on top rack and carrots on middle rack.)

Once veggies have roasted 10 minutes, pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; place between two large pieces of #plastic wrap{}. Pound with a #mallet{} or #rolling pin{} until chicken is about 1/2 inch thick. Season all over with @garlic powder{1%teaspoon}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add chicken; cook until browned and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side. TIP: Lower heat if chicken begins to brown too quickly.

Transfer chicken to a #cutting board{}.

In a #large bowl{}, combine @arugula{2%ounce}, roasted carrots, and @blue cheese dressing{1.5%ounce}.

Slice chicken crosswise.

Divide arugula and blue cheese salad and potato wedges between plates in separate sections. Top salad with chicken and garnish with @walnuts{0.5%ounce}. Serve.

> Poultry is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.